## What I learned
Today I learned how to use Burp Suite more efficiently by reducing noisy traffic and focusing on important requests.

## Key concepts
- HTTP history = all captured requests
- Site map = structure of the target application
- In-scope items = only traffic related to the target
- Static files = images, CSS, JS, fonts (usually less interesting first)
- Interesting requests = requests with parameters, forms, logins, search, IDs

## Interesting endpoints I found
- /search.php
- /artists.php?artist=1
- /product.php?id=1

## Repeater target
I sent one parameterized request to Repeater for later testing.

## Key insight
Not every request matters. Good recon means finding the requests that are actually worth testing.
